concept_explanation.streaming_types:
**Four gRPC communication patterns:**

```protobuf
service ZerodhaMarket {
  // Unary: one request, one response
  rpc GetQuote(QuoteRequest) returns (Quote);

  // Server streaming: one request, many responses (market feed)
  rpc WatchQuotes(WatchRequest) returns (stream Quote);

  // Client streaming: many requests, one response (batch upload)
  rpc UploadTrades(stream TradeRecord) returns (UploadSummary);

  // Bidirectional: many requests, many responses (live order book)
  rpc OrderBook(stream OrderRequest) returns (stream OrderUpdate);
}
```

concept_explanation.server_streaming:
**Server streaming implementation:**

```java
// Server: keep sending until cancelled or done
@GrpcService
public class MarketDataService extends ZerodhaMarketGrpc.ZerodhaMarketImplBase {
    @Override
    public void watchQuotes(WatchRequest req,
                            StreamObserver<Quote> responseObserver) {
        // Cast to check for cancellation:
        ServerCallStreamObserver<Quote> serverObserver =
            (ServerCallStreamObserver<Quote>) responseObserver;

        // Register cancel handler (client disconnects):
        serverObserver.setOnCancelHandler(() -> {
            log.info('Client cancelled quote stream for: {}', req.getSymbol());
            // Clean up resources (remove from subscription list)
        });

        // Push quotes until cancelled:
        ScheduledExecutorService scheduler = Executors.newSingleThreadScheduledExecutor();
        scheduler.scheduleAtFixedRate(() -> {
            if (serverObserver.isCancelled()) {
                scheduler.shutdown();
                return;
            }
            Quote quote = buildQuote(req.getSymbol());
            serverObserver.onNext(quote); // send one update
        }, 0, 100, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS); // every 100ms

        // Note: for infinite streams, DON'T call onCompleted()
        // The stream stays open until client cancels or error
    }
}
```

